snippet: More than 1.1 million people signed up for health insurance through federal and state marketplaces in January, according to the government.
abstract: Department of Health and Human Services reports that more than 1.1 million people signed up for health insurance through federal and state marketplaces in Jan 2014, as key youth demographic enrolled at faster rate than any other group; brings total to 3.3 million in first four months of enrollment; results are hailed by Obama administration, but are unlikely to tamp down political fight over the Affordable Care Act in lead-up to midterm elections.

byline.original: By MICHAEL D. SHEAR and REED ABELSON

lead_paragraph: More than 1.1 million people signed up for health insurance through federal and state marketplaces in January, according to the government.
